{"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GUI app or the "},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI — both backed by the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"},{"type":"text","text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a future release."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"],"syntax":"bash"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use "},{"code":"spook clone","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","level":3},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Spooktacular."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"+","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button or press "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cmd+N","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a new VM bundle."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Managing-VMs","text":"Managing VMs","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"syntax":"bash"},{"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CapacityCheck","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for details."}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"syntax":"bash"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"ssh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. See "},{"code":"ProvisioningMode","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed guidance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","text":"EC2 Mac Setup","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"release. See "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for the planned architecture."}]}]}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"]}],"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GitHubActionsGuide":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Configuring GitHub Actions Runners","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/githubactionsguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run self-hosted macOS GitHub Actions runners in Spooktacular VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RemoteDesktop":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Remote Desktop Access","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/remotedesktop","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Spooktacular VMs via VNC for remote development, QA testing, and design review."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/EC2MacDeployment":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Deploying on EC2 Mac","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/ec2macdeployment","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac dedicated hosts to double your macOS CI capacity."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/KubernetesGuide":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Kubernetes Integration","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/kubernetesguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources using the MacOSVM custom resource definition."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/OpenClawGuide":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit","title":"SpooktacularKit","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Machine Learning Workloads","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/mlworkloads","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/BlueBubblesGuide":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/bluebubblesguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Set up a BlueBubbles iMessage server in a macOS VM — a dramatically simpler alternative to VMware on Windows."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CLIReference":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/clireference","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines from the terminal with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI."}]}}}